The paper proposes a game-theoretic model for analyzing the strategic behavior of miners in the Bitcoin protocol. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. Additionally, the paper deals with the security and incentives of the blockchain protocol, which could also place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The paper also uses stochastic processes to model the behavior of miners, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT) categories.
